            <div id="org-structure" class="tab-pane active">
                <h2>Organizational Structure & Reorganizations</h2>
                <p><strong>Note:</strong> Booz Allen's structure is broadly organized by **Market (e.g., Defense, National Security, Civil)** and **Functional/Tech Capability (e.g., Cyber, AI, Engineering)**, often leveraging a matrix organization to bring capability teams to market sectors.</p>
                <div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
                    
                    <p style="font-style: italic; margin-top: 10px;">Simplified Visual Hierarchy (Replace with a formal Visio/Lucidchart diagram for presentation)</p>
                </div>
                <h3>Recent Reorganizations & Strategic Shifts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Continuous Shift to Solutions/Technology Focus:</strong> Ongoing reorganization to emphasize **Artificial Intelligence, Cyber, and Digital Engineering** as core offerings, moving beyond traditional pure consulting/staff augmentation. This is reflected in the creation/elevation of technology-focused leadership roles.</li>
                    <li><strong>Global Headquarters Relocation (2027 Projected):</strong> Announced relocation of Global HQ from McLean to **Reston, Virginia**. This move is positioned as a strategic shift to an "innovative, optimized" facility that supports advanced technology capabilities and rightsizes the facilities footprint.</li>
                    <li><strong>Acquisitions-Driven Integration:</strong> Reorganizations often follow key acquisitions (e.g., EverWatch, PGSC) to integrate new, specialized technology capabilities into the Defense and National Security sectors.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

